{"questionId":"29448853","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>One of the goats, Brenda, fights with the other goats. The farmer plans to place a second fence with a fixed length of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math> metres between the wall and the hedge to form a small triangular field inside <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OAB</mi></math> for Brenda.</p>\n<p>The information is shown on the following diagram.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/70de0d2dff356e6ec50e1b47ba9362f15f9bbe20.png\" width=\"671\" height=\"269\"></p>\n<p>The small triangular field <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OCD</mi></math> has an area of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> be the distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OC</mi></math> and let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> be the distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OD</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the two possible sizes of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>, giving your answers in degrees.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use the sine rule to find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>28</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>50</mn><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mstyle><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>69</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8748</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;or&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>110</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>125</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for each value.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempt to find at least one possible angle for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>180</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>69</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8748</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>180</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>110</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>125</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>82</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1251</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>41</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8748</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OAB</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>82</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>41</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use the cosine rule to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OB</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>25</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>50</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>OB</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mn>50</mn></mfenced><mfenced><mi>OB</mi></mfenced><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>28</mn><mo>°</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OB</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>52</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7491</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>35</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5455</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use the sine rule to find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>28</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>OB</mi><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mstyle><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>82</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1251</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>41</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8748</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>82</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>41</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"29448853","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ1.9ai","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the two possible sizes of OA^B, giving your answers in degrees.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.5—Unit circle definitions of sin, cos, tan. Exact trig ratios, ambiguous case of sine rule"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
